{"author":{"id":"f270607f232f5ea3e06daa2368d41de7674a6d0d64158946f2581dde2c4881fc"},"ops":[{"type":6,"timestamp":1734014165,"nonce":"5F4prREXC1NSpB1zTs7nIx9CgwQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lAHOAW4Y0s6jFWH3zmyPidg"},"target":"08aad0bdeb632af0700c71104c932f023e9d85dcee7a4b020819af2bed1dc064","message":"Currently, both wrappers require *maker* and unconditionally run the `maker2zff` [script](https://github.com/Yandell-Lab/maker/blob/master/src/bin/maker2zff) with default settings over the annotation gff with the aim of only retaining high-quality annotations for training.\n\nThis approach is suboptimal in several ways:\n1. The default behavior of `maker2zff` is to filter features based on qi and aed attribute values if the feature states maker in its source column. When source is not maker no filtering is performed.\n\n    All of this happens behind the scene without telling the user who doesn't know that maker and non-maker gffs are treated differently.\n\n2. The built-in filtering means the user cannot decide to apply less strict criteria than the default ones (unless they know about the secret workaround to disable default filtering by removing maker from the gff source column.\n3. If default filtering results in all features getting eliminated augustus and snap training fails with hard to diagnose errors.\n    Augustus example: `Error: training set file jwd05e/76659517/working/genome.gff3 has neither Genbank nor GFF nor FASTA format!` from which it is very hard to deduce that genome.gff3 is the filtered intermediate file and that it's simply empty.\n\nSuggestion:\nOffer a separate wrapper for `maker2zff` with full control over settings and only suggest to filter the input gff in the downstream tools.","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1734014203,"nonce":"P7DJL21326nsw35/NojT+f4FcTk=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lAHOAW4Y0s6jFWH3zmyPjkc"},"target":"08aad0bdeb632af0700c71104c932f023e9d85dcee7a4b020819af2bed1dc064","message":"Currently, both wrappers require *maker* and unconditionally run the `maker2zff` [script](https://github.com/Yandell-Lab/maker/blob/master/src/bin/maker2zff) with default settings over the annotation gff with the aim of only retaining high-quality annotations for training.\n\nThis approach is suboptimal in several ways:\n1. The default behavior of `maker2zff` is to filter features based on qi and aed attribute values if the feature states maker in its source column. When source is not maker no filtering is performed.\n\n    All of this happens behind the scene without telling the user who doesn't know that maker and non-maker gffs are treated differently.\n\n2. The built-in filtering means the user cannot decide to apply less strict criteria than the default ones (unless they know about the secret workaround to disable default filtering by removing maker from the gff source column).\n3. If default filtering results in all features getting eliminated augustus and snap training fails with hard to diagnose errors.\n    Augustus example: `Error: training set file jwd05e/76659517/working/genome.gff3 has neither Genbank nor GFF nor FASTA format!` from which it is very hard to deduce that genome.gff3 is the filtered intermediate file and that it's simply empty.\n\nSuggestion:\nOffer a separate wrapper for `maker2zff` with full control over settings and only suggest to filter the input gff in the downstream tools.","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1734014240,"nonce":"mRm4Y3iOT2Zx7wL0soE7gkncqUc=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lAHOAW4Y0s6jFWH3zmyPktM"},"target":"08aad0bdeb632af0700c71104c932f023e9d85dcee7a4b020819af2bed1dc064","message":"Currently, both wrappers require *maker* and unconditionally run the `maker2zff` [script](https://github.com/Yandell-Lab/maker/blob/master/src/bin/maker2zff) with default settings over the annotation gff with the aim of only retaining high-quality annotations for training.\n\nThis approach is suboptimal in several ways:\n1. The default behavior of `maker2zff` is to filter features based on qi and aed attribute values if the feature states maker in its source column. When source is not maker no filtering is performed.\n\n    All of this happens behind the scene without telling the user who doesn't know that maker and non-maker gffs are treated differently.\n\n2. The built-in filtering means the user cannot decide to apply less strict criteria than the default ones (unless they know about the secret workaround to disable default filtering by removing maker from the gff source column).\n3. If default filtering results in all features getting eliminated augustus and snap training fails with hard to diagnose errors.\n    Augustus example: `Error: training set file jwd05e/76659517/working/genome.gff3 has neither Genbank nor GFF nor FASTA format!` from which it is very hard to deduce that genome.gff3 is the filtered intermediate file and that it's simply empty.\n\nSuggestion:\nOffer a separate wrapper for `maker2zff` with full control over settings and only *suggest* to filter the input gff in the downstream tools.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1734014144,"nonce":"i065LI7fU/zkmaQX8pmNna+VcYs=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s6XWArc","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/6623#issuecomment-2539129564"},"message":"@abretaud @rlibouba what do you think?","files":null},{"type":5,"timestamp":1734014307,"nonce":"cqodbruVfH5kBiU4O6i3Bw8oS3U=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOAW4Y0s6jFWH3zwAAAAOj-AXP"},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]}]}